The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Ricoh charts growth plans

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Oct. 19: Ricoh India Limited (RIL), which recently announced its merger with Gestetner India, is eyeing a 30 per cent market share in office automation products over three years.

 At present, the company enjoys a market share of approximately 26 per cent.

 According to officials, Japan-based Ricoh has just received the nod from the high court for the merger of its two Indian subsidiaries ? Gestetner India and Ricoh India, which currently employs 922 people.

 According to the merger terms, shareholders will get six shares of Ricoh for every one of Gestetner held.

 After the merger, we will re-size the workforce. We will take appropriate action on reducing, increasing or rationalising the headcount. We may need to re-deploy people, Ricoh India president and CEO K. Swetharanyan said.

 Ricoh India, which reported a sales revenue of Rs 150 crore in 2004-05, is targeting a turnover of Rs 172 crore from its Indian operations this year, said Norifumi Fukuda, manager (international business group), Ricoh Company Limited, Japan.

 We are eyeing a 15 per cent growth this year, he said.

 Meanwhile, the parent company is planning to develop software in eight Indian languages for schools.

 Ricoh director Katsumi Yoshida ruled out a research and development base in the country in the near future. 




